.TH "DOTM" "8" "" "dotm" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
dotm \[em] declarative dotfiles manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]dotm\f[R] \f[B]init\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]dotm\f[R] \f[B]apply\f[R] [\f[B]\-n\f[R]|\f[B]\[en]dry\-run\f[R]]
.PP
\f[B]dotm\f[R] \f[B]diff\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]dotm\f[R] \f[B]status\f[R] [\f[B]\-v\f[R]|\f[B]\[en]verbose\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-q\f[R]|\f[B]\[en]quiet\f[R]]
.PP
\f[B]dotm\f[R] \f[B]reset\f[R] \f[I]NAME\f[R]\&...
.PP
\f[B]dotm\f[R] \f[B]reset\f[R] \f[B]\[en]all\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]dotm\f[R] [\f[B]\-h\f[R]|\f[B]\[en]help\f[R]]
.PP
\f[B]dotm\f[R] [\f[B]\-V\f[R]|\f[B]\[en]version\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]dotm\f[R] is a declarative dotfiles manager.
It reads configuration from \f[B]dotm.toml\f[R], walks a
\f[B]files/\f[R] directory, renders templates, writes to a destination
directory, applies permissions, and runs lifecycle scripts.
.PP
Configuration is read from \f[B]dotm.toml\f[R], searched from the
current directory upward.
State is stored in \f[B]\[ti]/.local/state/dotm/\f[R].
.PP
Unlike other dotfiles managers, dotm uses normal file paths (no magic
prefixes), delegates encryption to external tools (sops, age), and
supports first\-class permission management for system files.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]init\f[R]
Run interactive prompts, resolve template values, and create the state
cache.
Must be run at least once before \f[B]apply\f[R].
Re\-run to re\-answer prompts.
.TP
\f[B]apply\f[R]
Walk \f[B]files/\f[R], render templates, write to \f[B]dest\f[R], create
symlinks, apply permissions from the \f[B]perms\f[R] file, and run
lifecycle scripts.
Records a manifest for orphan detection.
.RS
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\[en]dry\-run\f[R]
Show what would happen without making any changes.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]diff\f[R]
Show a unified diff between rendered source and current destination for
each managed file.
.TP
\f[B]status\f[R]
Show the sync state of all managed files.
Four states are reported:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]clean\f[R]
Destination matches rendered source.
.TP
\f[B]modified\f[R]
Destination differs from rendered source.
.TP
\f[B]missing\f[R]
In source but not yet in destination.
.TP
\f[B]orphan\f[R]
Previously deployed, no longer in source, still in destination.
.TP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\[en]verbose\f[R]
Include clean files in the output.
.TP
\f[B]\-q\f[R], \f[B]\[en]quiet\f[R]
Exit 1 if any problems exist, produce no output.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]reset\f[R]
Reset cached prompt value(s).
After resetting, run \f[B]dotm init\f[R] to re\-answer prompts.
.RS
.TP
\f[I]NAME\f[R] [\f[I]NAME\f[R]\&...]
Reset specific prompt(s).
Errors if a name is not found.
.TP
\f[B]\[en]all\f[R]
Reset all cached values.
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\[en]help\f[R]
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
\f[B]\-V\f[R], \f[B]\[en]version\f[R]
Print program name and version, then exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Create \f[B]dotm.toml\f[R] in your dotfiles repository.
.IP
.EX
dest = \[dq]\[ti]\[dq]

\f[B][prompts]\f[R]
use_nvidia = { type = \[dq]bool\[dq], question = \[dq]Enable NVIDIA config?\[dq] }
git_email  = { type = \[dq]string\[dq], question = \[dq]Git email address\[dq] }

\f[B][symlinks]\f[R]
\[dq].local/bin/editor\[dq] = \[dq]{{ .homeDir }}/.nix\-profile/bin/nvim\[dq]

\f[B][[scripts]]\f[R]
path = \[dq]scripts/reload.sh\[dq]
template = true
trigger = \[dq]on_change\[dq]
.EE
.SS Options
.TP
\f[B]dest\f[R]
Destination directory.
Use \f[B]\[lq]/\[rq]\f[R] for system\-wide configuration.
Supports \f[B]\[ti]\f[R] prefix for home directory.
Default: \f[B]\[ti]\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]shell\f[R]
Shell for script execution.
Default: \f[B]bash\f[R].
.TP
\f[B][prompts]\f[R]
Interactive prompts with values available in templates.
Types: \f[B]bool\f[R] or \f[B]string\f[R].
.TP
\f[B][symlinks]\f[R]
Map of symlink paths (relative to \f[B]dest\f[R]) to targets.
Targets may contain template expressions.
.TP
\f[B][[scripts]]\f[R]
Lifecycle scripts to run after apply.
\f[B]path\f[R] \[em] relative to source directory.
\f[B]template\f[R] \[em] render as template before running.
Default: \f[B]false\f[R].
\f[B]trigger\f[R] \[em] \f[B]always\f[R] or \f[B]on_change\f[R].
Default: \f[B]always\f[R].
